    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Problem</h1>
            <h4>Checkout is the commitment layer of the marketplace journey. By the time users reach checkout, they are no longer trying to explore every option. They are trying to confirm the rental, resolve required logistics, pay, and know what happens next. </h4>
            <h4>The redesign focused on protecting that commitment moment by removing nonessential tasks, resolving identity earlier, preventing late-stage account errors, and making the final order easy to review before purchase. </h4>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
